WEBVTT

00:06.198 --> 00:08.499
All right, try it now.

00:12.922 --> 00:15.690
And there you have it.

00:15.692 --> 00:16.841
How'd you do that?

00:16.843 --> 00:18.192
Oh, did the same thing
I always do.

00:18.194 --> 00:20.278
I wiggled some wires around
until it started.

00:20.280 --> 00:22.663
You know, we got
to stop meeting like this.

00:22.665 --> 00:24.482
You, me,
and this pile of junk.

00:24.484 --> 00:26.651
Well, we can't
afford to fix it.

00:26.653 --> 00:28.335
Not with the boys'
tuition hikes.

00:28.337 --> 00:31.005
Speaking of which, I got an
estimate for the carpet repair.

00:31.007 --> 00:32.557
Yeah? And?

00:32.558 --> 00:34.525
It's as crappy
as the carpet.

00:34.527 --> 00:36.010
Great.

00:36.012 --> 00:38.210
So, what? Can you get another
loan on your pension?

00:38.235 --> 00:38.697
No.

00:38.698 --> 00:40.148
We maxed that out
already, babe.

00:40.150 --> 00:41.532
So what's the plan?

00:41.534 --> 00:44.952
The plan now is for you
to drive this beater home.

00:44.954 --> 00:47.205
Straight home and
do not stop, okay?

00:47.207 --> 00:49.540
And most of all,
do not worry about money.

00:49.542 --> 00:51.709
We'll be fine.

00:51.711 --> 00:54.829
Wait. What do I do
if that weird noise comes back?

00:54.831 --> 00:56.748
Just turn up the radio.

00:58.801 --> 01:00.451
Love you.

01:00.453 --> 01:02.053
Love you more.

01:02.055 --> 01:04.221
Love you most.

01:11.096 --> 01:13.097
Something smells good.

01:13.099 --> 01:14.682
Oh, <i>sí, señor.</i>

01:14.684 --> 01:16.884
My world-famous chili.

01:19.721 --> 01:23.691
Drink before dinner. Thanks.

01:23.693 --> 01:25.893
Cheers.
Cheers.

01:28.197 --> 01:31.199
Favorite part of my day--
dinner with my old man.

01:33.569 --> 01:36.454
Are you, uh, buttering me up
for some reason,

01:36.456 --> 01:37.872
Francis?

01:37.874 --> 01:40.041
I'm just happy to see you, Pop.

01:41.093 --> 01:44.762
So... how was your day?

01:44.764 --> 01:47.799
Great, honey. Yours?

01:52.137 --> 01:54.055
You got something on your mind,
spit it.

01:54.057 --> 01:56.257
What makes you think
I got something on my mind?

01:56.259 --> 01:58.192
You're not the only guy
in this room

01:58.194 --> 02:00.027
who used to wear
a gold shield, Francis.

02:00.029 --> 02:02.647
And when I was wearing mine,
you were wearing diapers.

02:05.217 --> 02:07.151
Well... I did notice

02:07.153 --> 02:10.571
there was a pretty big dent
in the bumper of your car.

02:10.573 --> 02:11.823
Oh, here we go.

02:11.825 --> 02:13.908
No, I'm just asking
what happened.

02:13.910 --> 02:15.209
No, you're insinuating.

02:15.211 --> 02:16.610
I'm not insinuating anything.

02:16.612 --> 02:18.779
The hell you're not.
You think I don't know

02:18.781 --> 02:20.464
what I'm doing
behind the wheel anymore.

02:20.466 --> 02:23.134
I'm just asking
what happened to your car.

02:23.136 --> 02:24.385
How would I know?

02:24.387 --> 02:25.887
I went into Ziggy's for lunch.

02:25.889 --> 02:27.955
I came out,
I had a busted bumper.

02:27.957 --> 02:30.007
So somebody hit you
when you were inside?

02:30.009 --> 02:31.392
Excellent police work.

02:31.394 --> 02:34.178
And they didn't leave a note?
Are you finished?

02:34.180 --> 02:36.681
Damn it, Pop,
you shouldn't be driving!

02:37.533 --> 02:39.483
Go to hell!

